# Alak, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Alak (; ) is a rural locality (a selo) in Botlikhsky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia. The population was 2,764 as of 2010. There are 32 streets.
Geography
Alak is located 14&nbsp;km southwest of Botlikh (the district's administrative centre) by road. Kheleturi is the nearest rural locality.
